quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  41,33,"And who speaks better than he who calls others to the worship of God, does what is right, and says: ‘I am a Muslim‘"
  41,34,"Good deeds and evil deeds are not equal. Requite evil with what is better and lo, he who is your enemy now will become as if your intimate friend"
  41,35,But none will attain this attribute save those who patiently endure; and none will attain it save those who are immensely fortunate
  41,36,"If Satan tempts you, seek refuge in God. He it is who hears all and knows all"
  41,37,"Among His signs are the night and the day, and the sun and the moon. But do not prostrate yourselves before the sun or the moon; rather prostrate yourselves before God, who created them both, if you would truly serve Him"
  41,38,"If they¹ disdain His service, let them remember that those who dwell with God give glory to Him night and day and are never wearied"
  41,39,"And yet another of His signs is that you behold the earth humble and desolate: but when We send down the rain upon it, it stirs and swells. He that gives it life will surely raise the dead to life. He has power over all things"
  41,40,"Those that deny Our revelations are not hidden from Our view. Is he who is cast into the Fire better off than he who emerges safe on the Day of Resurrection? Do as you will, He observes whatever you do"
  41,41,Those who deny the Admonition when it is preached to them ― and surely it is a momentous Book
  41,42,falsehood cannot reach it from before or from behind. It is a revelation from a wise and praiseworthy God
  41,43,"Nothing is said to you that has not been said to other apostles before you. Your Lord is forgiving, but stern in retribution"
  41,44,"Had We revealed it a Koran in a foreign tongue they would have said: ‘If only its verses were expounded! Why in a foreign tongue, and he an Arabian?‘ Say: ‘To true believers it is a guide and a healing balm. But those who deny it are deaf and blind: they are called to from a far-off place.‘"